text: The Waco: Rye with trout, celery, and Vegemite.
The Apostle: Cheese, usually mozzarella, and kimchi between two slices of grilled baguette.
The Hyena: Grilled baguette with blackened tuna, kimchi, and Russian dressing.
The Lecturer: Feta, veggie burger, onions and sweet onions in a hollowed-out onion roll.
The Lemur: Smoked tuna with melted Gruyere on rye, covered in mushrooms and wasabi.
The Ontario: A picked or soft-boiled egg, provolone and prosciutto served on a buttered brioche bun.
The Cabby: A grilled roll containing a poached or scrambled egg and mushrooms. Typically prepared with salsa.
The Boulder: Cheese, often mozzarella, and watercress between two slices of grilled pumpernickel.
The Gavin: Feta, lettuce, and red peppers between two slices of ciabatta.
The Monkey: A poached egg with pepper jack and mozzarella on focaccia, covered in shredded carrots, broccoli, and hummus.
The Toad: Focaccia with bacon, cucumber, and mustard.
The Paramedic: A grilled wheat roll containing turkey pastrami and cucumber. Prepared with jalapeno.
The Ferret: Toasted sourdough with pork, white onions, and hoisin sauce.
The Lakeland: Pepper jack and avocado between two slices of grilled white bread.
The Banker: Ciabatta with blackened ahi, broccoli, and salsa.
The Hartford: A tortilla wrap filled with duck sausage and green olives, usually served with horseradish.
The Advisor: Duck sausage with feta on focaccia, covered in watercress, sauerkraut, and giardiniera.
The Lowell: Cheese, often Havarti, and lettuce between two slices of toasted pain de mie.
The Nevaeh: Typically a picked or poached egg, gorgonzola and bacon served on a poppy seed bun.
The Allison: Cheese, traditionally mozzarella, and brussel sprouts between two slices of toasted focaccia.
The Richmond: A sourdough roll containing polenta, broccoli, and red peppers. Often eaten with guacamole.
The Empress: A lavash wrap filled with duck sausage and red peppers, usually served with mustard.
The Warthog: Ciabatta stuffed with chicken, duck, chorizo, melted pepper jack, and spinach topped with ranch dressing.
The Bellevue: A buckwheat wrap filled with veggie sausage, basil, and cucumber, usually served with wasabi.
The Midland: A tortilla wrap filled with smoked tilapia, avocado, and cucumber, usually served with olive oil.
The Retailer: Andouille, served on a toasted bun, usually with olives, chard, and horseradish.
The Developer: Havarti, ham, cornichons and red cabbage in a hollowed-out wheat roll.
The Commander: Fried egg, served on a bun, usually with brussel sprouts, cucumber, and salsa.
The Springfield: Cheese, gorgonzola, and spinach between two slices of toasted ciabatta.
The Broken Arrow: A toasted wheat roll containing duck sausage and red cabbage. Typically eaten with pesto.
The Wombat: Sourdough with pork sausage, kimchi, and spicy mustard.
The Vallejo: American cheese, scrambled egg, red onions and sprouts in a hollowed-out pumpernickel roll.
The Assistant: Cheese, white cheddar, and kale between two slices of toasted sourdough.
The Gopher: Provolone, blackened catfish, kimchi and lettuce in a hollowed-out challah roll.
The Robert: A scrambled or hard-boiled egg, Jarlsberg and smoked pork served on a toasted poppy seed bun.
The Natalie: A poached or scrambled egg, Jarlsberg and ground beef served on a grilled yeast bun.
The Wildcat: Cheese, traditionally gorgonzola, and basil between two slices of ciabatta.
The Nurse: Veggie sausage with melted muenster on challah, slathered in sauerkraut, watercress, and fennel.
The Elder: A scrambled or fried egg, cheddar and ground bison served on a toasted yeast bun.
The Elijah: Cheese, typically brie, and chili peppers between two slices of grilled bagel.
The Riley: A buckwheat wrap filled with kielbasa and chili peppers, usually served with salsa.
The Substitute Teacher: Multi-grain stuffed with chorizo sausage, Jarlsberg and Havarti, basil, and arugula covered in spicy mustard.
The Temecula: Ground bison, served on a grilled bun, usually with cucumber, watercress, and pickles.
The Joseph: White cheddar, chorizo sausage, kale and onions in a hollowed-out onion roll.
The Cat: Often a scrambled or soft-boiled egg, manchego and coppa served on a toasted poppy seed bun.
The Duchess: A toasted challah roll containing smoked tilapia and broccoli. Eaten with Marmite.
The Benjamin: Often a soft-boiled or poached egg, Gruyere and pastrami served on a toasted poppy seed bun.
The Queen: Sourdough stuffed with chorizo with a poached egg, melted muenster, radish greens, and basil topped with pesto.
The Cheetah: A pretzel roll containing turkey bacon with a fried egg and white onions. Often prepared with salsa.
The Wedding Planner: Seitan on challah (open-faced) with pickled daikon and tomato, slathered in horseradish.
The Programmer: Dutch crunch with veggie sausage, sauerkraut, and sriracha.
The Writer: Typically a poached or scrambled egg, Jarlsberg and lamb served on a toasted sesame bun.
The Columbia: Pain de mie stuffed with thinly sliced pork and turkey, melted limburger, red onions, and tomato slathered in giardiniera.
The Princess: Swiss and celery between two slices of bagel.
The Orangutan: Grilled crab with cheddar, Swiss on Dutch crunch, covered in chili peppers, and celery salt.
The Wyatt: Poached egg, served on a grilled bun, usually with red peppers, chard, and parsley.
The Buffalo: Havarti, pork sausage, red peppers and brussel sprouts in a hollowed-out roll.
The Tempe: A toasted roll containing tofu, chard, and beet greens. Often prepared with vinegar.
The Emma: A toasted challah roll containing black sausage and spinach. Often served with malt vinegar.
The Julian: Usually a poached or hard-boiled egg, limburger and chicken served on a toasted poppy seed bun.
The Evansville: A grilled wheat roll containing duck and bacon, lettuce, and sprouts. Prepared with mayonnaise.
The Eli: Quinoa with melted Monterey Jack on baguette, covered in chard and fennel.
The Ellie: Roast beef and coppa on ciabatta (open-faced) with collard greens, covered in vinegar.
The Matriarch: A pretzel roll containing pork, slaw, and red peppers. Usually eaten with hummus.
The Oceanside: Catfish on Dutch crunch (open-faced) with lettuce and brussel sprouts, covered in parsley.
The Grizzly Bear: Cheese, Havarti, and red cabbage between two slices of grilled spelt bread.
The Audrey: Polenta with cheddar, Havarti on white bread, topped with watercress, and guacamole.
The Donkey: Wheat bread stuffed with thickly sliced chicken with a picked egg, limburger, and onions covered in pepper jelly.
The Kelli: Poached egg, served on a grilled bun, usually with sauerkraut, pickled daikon, and Russian dressing.
The Peoria: Traditionally a poached or scrambled egg, Havarti and chicken served on a asiago bun.
The Newt: Challah stuffed with turkey bacon, pepper jack, and cucumber covered in pickles.
The Ocelot: A toasted roll containing fried chicken, spinach, and pickled daikon. Typically prepared with hot sauce.
The Layla: A spinach wrap filled with smoked crab, collard greens, and kale, usually served with malt vinegar.
The Nolan: A grilled pumpernickel roll containing turkey bacon and radish greens. Often eaten with aioli.
The Opossum: Ciabatta stuffed with ham, roast chicken, and turkey bacon, limburger, gorgonzola, and sprouts topped with pesto.
The Addison: Tuna salad on Dutch crunch (open-faced) with pickled daikon, topped with mayonnaise.
The Chameleon: A naan wrap filled with polenta and chili peppers, usually served with hoisin sauce.
The Yonkers: Turkey bacon, fried lamb with melted pepper jack on rye, slathered in chard, and pepper jelly.
The Hampton: A pita wrap filled with chorizo sausage and olives, usually served with olive oil.
The Tapir: Cheese, typically Gruyere, and pickled daikon between two slices of toasted bagel.
The Gnu: Pastrami and smoked chicken on Dutch crunch (open-faced) with lettuce, topped with malt vinegar.
The Deer: White bread stuffed with roast chicken, pastrami, and smoked lamb, muenster, onions, and sprouts topped with remoulade.
The Serenity: Seitan, served on a bun, usually with cucumber, shredded carrots, and malt vinegar.
The High Point: Toasted sourdough with fried crab, mushrooms, and olive oil.
The Hudson: Salami and roast chicken on rye (open-faced) with cornichons, covered in fennel.
The Aardvark: Cheese, usually limburger, and kale between two slices of toasted ciabatta.
The Instructor: Gorgonzola, kielbasa, eggplant and slaw in a hollowed-out pretzel roll.
The Woodchuck: A sourdough roll containing chicken salad and cornichons. Usually served with remoulade.
The Monarch: Bagel stuffed with a scrambled egg, melted Swiss, and red cabbage slathered in gravy.
The Abbess: Cheese, Monterey Jack, and chili peppers between two slices of grilled baguette.
The Pompano Beach: Limburger, salami, shredded carrots and slaw in a hollowed-out challah roll.
The Architect: Gorgonzola and olives between two slices of grilled sourdough.
The Gabriella: A soft-boiled egg on white bread (open-faced) with kale, covered in tzatziki.
The Miramar: Muenster, egg salad, artichoke hearts and lettuce in a hollowed-out onion roll.
The Sarah: Buttered bagel with tuna salad, pickled daikon, and giardiniera.
The Rochester: Cheese, usually limburger, and kale between two slices of buttered baguette.
The Colonel: Bagel with duck, onions, and pickles.
The Newport News: Tofu with brie on Dutch crunch, topped with sprouts, shredded carrots, and remoulade.
The Baron: Cheese, usually Swiss, and fried onions between two slices of grilled challah.
The Auctioneer: Chicken sausage on baguette (open-faced) with chard, topped with Marmite.
The Green Bay: Jarlsberg, blackened flounder, kale and avocado in a hollowed-out roll.
The Hippopotamus: Feta and sauerkraut between two slices of buttered sourdough.
The Daniel: Limburger, roast beef, shredded carrots and chili peppers in a hollowed-out sourdough roll.
The Lansing: Goat cheese, cucumber, and brussel sprouts between two slices of grilled spelt bread.
The Advertiser: Swiss and arugula between two slices of sourdough.
The Consultant: A fried or scrambled egg, brie and corned beef served on a buttered sesame bun.
The Andrew: White cheddar, corned beef, olives and chili peppers in a hollowed-out pretzel roll.
The Psychologist: Grilled pork, served on a bun, usually with lettuce, onions, and pickles.
The Beaumont: Blue cheese, flounder, slaw and lettuce in a hollowed-out onion roll.
The Actor: Pumpernickel with fried flounder, red cabbage, and wasabi.
The Bella: Baguette with sausage, cornichons, and gravy.
